00:24:52.600 --> 00:24:55.367
Oh no, I'm sorry, I didn't prepare anything.

00:25:03.267 --> 00:25:04.400
So good.

00:25:12.667 --> 00:25:14.600
Could it be...

00:25:15.433 --> 00:25:18.267
...that I'm a little lonely?

00:25:27.667 --> 00:25:29.233
Today was so fun.

00:25:29.233 --> 00:25:30.600
It was really fun.

00:25:30.600 --> 00:25:32.400
You have to take me again.

00:25:32.400 --> 00:25:33.733
Of course.

00:25:35.200 --> 00:25:36.300
But...

00:25:36.300 --> 00:25:38.267
I really want some ice cream.

00:25:38.267 --> 00:25:41.867
-Next time. -Next time? Will they still have that flavor?

00:25:42.300 --> 00:25:44.167
Doing that kind of thing in a place like this...

00:25:51.867 --> 00:25:55.000
But even when we're together, it feels kind of lonely.

00:26:03.000 --> 00:26:04.633
Awesome!

00:26:04.900 --> 00:26:06.933
When can we go?

00:26:07.700 --> 00:26:09.000
Next week.

00:26:09.000 --> 00:26:11.500
I really want some ice cream.

00:26:11.500 --> 00:26:13.600
-Next time. -Will they still have that flavor?

00:26:13.600 --> 00:26:15.333
Doing that kind of thing in a place like this...

00:26:25.933 --> 00:26:27.300
What's wrong?

00:26:29.067 --> 00:26:30.533
What is it?

00:26:32.667 --> 00:26:34.467
Back then, I was so self-conscious...

00:26:34.900 --> 00:26:37.067
...I didn't even dare to hold her hand outside.

00:26:41.733 --> 00:26:43.067
Sorry to keep you waiting.

00:26:43.067 --> 00:26:45.267
Time for a drink.

00:27:00.733 --> 00:27:02.933
I wonder what Ayumi is doing right now.

00:27:20.633 --> 00:27:23.000
-Morning. -Morning.

00:27:23.000 --> 00:27:24.700
I'm so hungover...

00:27:24.933 --> 00:27:26.133
Where did you go?

00:27:26.133 --> 00:27:27.533
Shichimon-ya.

00:27:27.533 --> 00:27:28.767
You really love that place.

00:27:28.767 --> 00:27:31.567
The grilled offal there is so good.

00:27:31.567 --> 00:27:33.567
Especially the shiro and kashira.

00:27:33.567 --> 00:27:37.133
I could eat shiro and kashira with whiskey and coke for the rest of my life.

00:27:40.133 --> 00:27:41.333
I think I'm gonna be sick.

00:27:48.367 --> 00:27:50.600
I can't believe I came here.

00:27:58.700 --> 00:28:01.367
(Kashira, Shiro)
What on earth are kashira and shiro?

00:28:01.367 --> 00:28:02.600
They're delicious.

00:28:03.033 --> 00:28:05.033
Then I'll have the kashira and shiro.

00:28:05.033 --> 00:28:06.767
And to drink, I'll have...

00:28:08.100 --> 00:28:10.233
-A whiskey and coke. -Right away.

00:28:11.567 --> 00:28:13.133
Why is he here?

00:28:14.200 --> 00:28:15.333
Miss.

00:28:15.667 --> 00:28:17.567
The young lady who was looking for tequila.

00:28:21.700 --> 00:28:24.267
-You're the guy from the liquor store... -Please wait.

00:28:28.733 --> 00:28:30.967
-Good evening. -Good evening.

00:28:30.967 --> 00:28:36.000
I'm looking for appetizers to pair with a new tequila I got in.

00:28:36.667 --> 00:28:38.967
Would you like to come and try some with me?

00:28:40.067 --> 00:28:43.800
No, I'm not a very good drinker.

00:28:45.100 --> 00:28:47.200
It's this one.

00:28:48.033 --> 00:28:49.633
Have a little.

00:28:52.333 --> 00:28:53.533
Kashira and shiro.

00:28:53.533 --> 00:28:55.100
Let's eat.

00:28:58.033 --> 00:28:59.467
So delicious.

00:29:01.900 --> 00:29:03.400
It goes down so smooth.

00:29:06.133 --> 00:29:09.100
Delicious. I see.

00:29:09.567 --> 00:29:11.633
So this is pork cheek.

00:29:12.933 --> 00:29:14.767
I see.

00:29:15.667 --> 00:29:18.667
Then what is shiro?

00:29:22.233 --> 00:29:23.600
Delicious.

00:29:27.900 --> 00:29:30.067
I guess you never know until you try.

00:29:30.067 --> 00:29:31.633
Exactly.

00:29:32.033 --> 00:29:34.833
Here's your whiskey and coke.

00:29:40.600 --> 00:29:42.833
-So good. -Glad you like it.

00:29:43.667 --> 00:29:45.033
By the way...

00:29:45.700 --> 00:29:47.933
I want to see if this drink suits these kinds of appetizers.

00:29:47.933 --> 00:29:48.867
Yakitori?

00:29:48.867 --> 00:29:50.200
And sushi.

00:29:50.867 --> 00:29:53.000
Shouldn't the side dish be Mexican food?

00:29:53.000 --> 00:29:56.000
I want to find appetizers that are more readily available.

00:29:56.000 --> 00:29:58.500
To make tequila more approachable.

00:29:59.100 --> 00:30:00.500
Will it really match?

00:30:00.500 --> 00:30:06.400
Let's give it a try and find out.

00:30:06.933 --> 00:30:08.067
Okay.

00:30:11.133 --> 00:30:12.333
So sweet.

00:30:13.933 --> 00:30:22.500
But the aroma of the spices makes the taste of the offal refreshing.

00:30:23.433 --> 00:30:24.633
I see.

00:30:24.633 --> 00:30:26.900
How's the whiskey and coke?

00:30:27.667 --> 00:30:28.800
You were here?

00:30:28.800 --> 00:30:30.367
I was. I saw you, too.

00:30:30.367 --> 00:30:32.700
What? You should've said something.

00:30:33.700 --> 00:30:37.167
I'm in the process of opening a new window in my life.

00:30:38.667 --> 00:30:40.400
It goes well with oden, too.

00:30:40.400 --> 00:30:41.833
-Really? -Yeah.

00:30:42.467 --> 00:30:44.367
This is fun.

00:30:44.367 --> 00:30:46.167
-Right? -Yes.

00:30:51.100 --> 00:30:53.333
I can't stop drinking this tequila.

00:30:54.833 --> 00:31:00.033
When you discover something new, it's as if the world has expanded.

00:31:00.033 --> 00:31:01.467
It's fun, isn't it?

00:31:02.233 --> 00:31:03.667
It really is fun.

00:31:03.667 --> 00:31:05.267
-Right? -Yeah.

00:31:06.933 --> 00:31:10.667
But you can really hold your liquor.

00:31:12.767 --> 00:31:15.700
Oh... that's true.

00:31:16.567 --> 00:31:19.433
Then why did you say you couldn't drink?

00:31:22.800 --> 00:31:27.633
The person I used to date...

00:31:27.633 --> 00:31:31.200
...was the type of person who thought all girls were light drinkers.

00:31:31.200 --> 00:31:33.433
I bought some more drinks.

00:31:33.433 --> 00:31:34.867
Thanks.

00:31:34.867 --> 00:31:35.667
What's everyone drinking?

00:31:35.667 --> 00:31:36.533
I'll have a shochu highball.

00:31:36.533 --> 00:31:37.633
-Me too. -Ayumi can just have oolong tea.

00:31:37.633 --> 00:31:39.267
Here, oolong tea.

00:31:40.233 --> 00:31:41.933
You can't drink much, so you don't have to.

00:31:42.267 --> 00:31:44.600
What a reliable guy. So cool.

00:31:44.600 --> 00:31:46.967
Even though I could actually drink more...

00:31:47.633 --> 00:31:50.767
...to be the perfect girlfriend...

00:31:50.767 --> 00:31:53.433
...I had to pretend I was a light drinker.

00:31:54.600 --> 00:32:00.033
From that moment on,
I always tried to be the perfect girlfriend.

00:32:01.767 --> 00:32:09.433
Gradually, I lost sight of what I really thought.

00:32:12.133 --> 00:32:14.233
What a waste.

00:32:15.433 --> 00:32:19.933
He never got to see you enjoying a drink so happily.

00:32:22.267 --> 00:32:24.833
I, for one, would love to have a drink with you.

00:32:33.567 --> 00:32:35.033
-I'll have a beer. -Right away.

00:32:35.033 --> 00:32:37.533
Didn't you just say you opened a new window?

00:32:37.533 --> 00:32:40.833
I'm still a beer person, after all.

00:32:41.767 --> 00:32:43.933
But...

00:32:44.500 --> 00:32:48.633
...I think I understand a little why you feel happy drinking that.

00:32:49.900 --> 00:32:52.733
I've learned that there's a world I never knew.

00:32:52.733 --> 00:32:53.967
Here's your beer.

00:32:53.967 --> 00:32:54.900
Thanks.

00:32:54.900 --> 00:32:58.133
If you're always prejudiced, you can't broaden your horizons.

00:32:59.433 --> 00:33:01.000
Indeed.

00:33:06.600 --> 00:33:10.133
But your thoughts about this are probably related to your ex-girlfriend, right?

00:33:11.300 --> 00:33:14.933
-I bought more drinks. -Thanks.

00:33:14.933 --> 00:33:15.633
What's everyone drinking?

00:33:15.633 --> 00:33:16.467
Shochu highball for me.

00:33:16.467 --> 00:33:17.700
-Me too. -Ayumi can just have oolong tea.

00:33:17.700 --> 00:33:19.033
Here, oolong tea.

00:33:19.033 --> 00:33:21.200
You can't drink much, so you don't have to.

00:33:21.200 --> 00:33:23.167
-Thanks. -What a reliable guy. So cool.

00:33:23.167 --> 00:33:25.367
I was always just assuming things...

00:33:25.367 --> 00:33:28.700
...about what Ayumi probably wanted to eat or drink.

00:33:30.067 --> 00:33:32.100
I never noticed.

00:33:34.200 --> 00:33:37.900
But what she actually wanted...

00:33:38.900 --> 00:33:41.900
...I wouldn't know unless I asked her.

00:33:44.633 --> 00:33:47.000
You seem to have changed.

00:33:48.167 --> 00:33:49.433
You think?

00:33:49.433 --> 00:33:51.600
The guy I used to date...

00:33:51.600 --> 00:33:54.633
...would probably say that tequila is a flirty drink.

00:33:54.633 --> 00:33:56.467
There are still people like that?

00:33:56.900 --> 00:34:00.533
But I was like that until just recently.

00:34:00.533 --> 00:34:05.467
I thought tequila was only for flirty people...

00:34:05.467 --> 00:34:08.067
...and had nothing to do with me.

00:34:10.400 --> 00:34:11.867
Delicious.

00:34:14.100 --> 00:34:18.200
You're really cute.

00:34:19.700 --> 00:34:24.000
The way you enjoy your tequila is very cute.

00:34:30.800 --> 00:34:33.267
Look, your face is a little red.

00:34:33.267 --> 00:34:34.667
It is.

00:34:37.100 --> 00:34:38.600
Let's take a picture.

00:34:46.600 --> 00:34:48.000
Great shot.

00:34:48.633 --> 00:34:50.700
It really is.

00:34:56.400 --> 00:34:59.867
Oh, that reminds me.

00:35:01.233 --> 00:35:04.800
Are you left-handed by any chance?

00:35:05.900 --> 00:35:07.167
Yes.

00:35:07.167 --> 00:35:08.467
Me too.

00:35:08.467 --> 00:35:10.033
We're the same!

00:35:10.433 --> 00:35:11.667
Which hand do you use to eat?

00:35:11.667 --> 00:35:13.667
-My left hand. -Me too.

00:35:15.300 --> 00:35:16.167
What about throwing?

00:35:16.167 --> 00:35:18.133
I throw with my right hand.

00:35:18.300 --> 00:35:19.833
-Same here! -We're the same.

00:35:19.833 --> 00:35:22.467
When I first talked to Katsuo...

00:35:22.967 --> 00:35:25.333
...I completely forgot about his "conditions."

00:35:25.333 --> 00:35:28.233
It was a feeling that couldn't be explained by logic.

